I"’<p>The <code>emby</code> platform allows you to control a <a href="https://emby.media/">Emby</a> multimedia system from Home Assistant.</p>
<p>To add Emby to your installation, add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
media_player:
  - platform: emby
    host: YOUR_IP_ADDRESS
    api_key: YOUR_API_KEY
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='host' href='#host'></a> host</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The host name or IP address of the device that is running Emby.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>localhost</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='api_key' href='#api_key'></a> api_key</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The API key to use to authenticate.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='ssl' href='#ssl'></a> ssl</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='boolean'>boolean</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Connect with HTTPS/WSS. Your SSL certificate must be valid.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>false</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='port' href='#port'></a> port</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The port number of the device that is running Emby.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>8096 (No SSL),  8920 (SSL)</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
